obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43351)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43351&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Guardians and Wards Act,`
  line 1890.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***,`
  line
  line `^2** * ^3***`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1890.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line `2. The words "inclusive of British Baluchistan" rep by A.O. 1948.`
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by Act 40 of 1949, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43352)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43352&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43353)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Saving of jurisdiction of Courts of Wards and Chartered High Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43353&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall be`
  line `read subject to every enactment heretofore or hereafter passed relating to any Court of Wards by ^1[any competent legislature, authority or person in ^2`
  line `[any State to which this Act extends]], and nothing in this Act shall be construed to affect, or in any way derogate from the jurisdiction or authority of any`
  line `Court of Wards, or to take away any power possessed by ^3[any High Court ^4`
  line ***].
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the G.G. in C., or by a Governor or Lieutenant-Governor in Council".`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule for "Part A States and Part C States".`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "any High Court established under the Statute 24 and 25 Victoria, Ch. 104 (an Act for establishing High Courts of Judicature in India)."`
  line `4. The words "established in Part A States and Part C States" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43354)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43354&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `(1) "minor" means a person who, under the provisions of the Indian Majority Act, 1875, (9 of 1875) is to be deemed not to have attained his majority:`
  line
  line `(2) "guardian" means a person having the care of the person of a minor or of his property, or of both is person and property:`
  line
  line `(3) "ward" means a minor for whose person or property, or both, there is a guardian:`
  line
  line `(4) "District Court" has the meaning assigned to that expression in the ^1Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), and includes a High Court in the exercise of its ordinary original civil jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `^2[(5) "the Court" means--`
  line
  line `(a) the District Court having jurisdiction to entertain an application under this Act for an order appointing or declaring a person to be a guardian; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a guardian has been appointed or declared in pursuance of any such application--`
  line
  line `(i) the Court which, or the Court of the officer who, appointed or declared the guardian or is under this Act deemed to have appointed or declared the guardian; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any matter relating to the person of the ward the District Court having jurisdiction in the place where the ward for the time being ordinarily resides; or`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of any proceeding transferred under section 4A, the Court of the officer to whom such proceeding has been transferred:]`
  line
  line `(6) "Collector" means the chief officer in charge of the revenue administration of a district, and includes any officer whom the State Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, may, by name or in virtue of his office, appoint to be a Collector in any local area, or with respect to any class of persons, for all or any of the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `^3* * * *; and`
  line
  line `(8) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the High Court under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1926, s. 2, for the clause (5).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (7) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (43406)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to confer jurisdiction on subordinate judicial officers and to transfer proceedings to such officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1926, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43406&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Power to confer jurisdiction on subordinate judicial officers and to transfer`
  line `proceedings to such officers.—(1) The High Court may, by general or special order, empower any`
  line `officer exercising original civil jurisdiction subordinate to a District Court, or authorise the Judge of`
  line `any District Court to empower any such officer subordinate to him, to dispose of any proceedings`
  line `under this Act transferred to such officer under the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Judge of a District Court may, by order in writing, transfer at any stage any proceeding`
  line `under this Act pending in his Court for disposal to any officer subordinate to him empowered under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Judge of a District Court may at any stage transfer to his own Court or to any officer`
  line `subordinate to him empowered under sub-section (1) any proceeding under this Act pending in the`
  line `Court of any other such officer.`
  line
  line `(4) When any proceedings are transferred under this section in any case in which a guardian has`
  line `been appointed or declared, the Judge of the District Court may, by order in writing, declare that the`
  line `Court of the Judge or officer to whom they are transferred shall, for all or any of the purposes of this`
  line `Act, be deemed to be the Court which appointed or declared the guardian.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43356)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43356&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `[Power of parents to appoint in case of European British subjects.] Omitted by the Part B States`
  line `(Laws) Act, 1951 (3 of 1951), s. 3 and Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43357)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Saving of power to appoint in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. The words who is not an European British subject omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43357&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a minor ^1`
  line `***, nothing in this Act`
  line `shall be construed to take away or derogate from any power to appoint a guardian of his person or`
  line `property, or both, which is valid by the law to which the minor is subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43358)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of the Court to make order as to guardianship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43358&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) where the Court is satisfied that`
  line `it is for the welfare of a minor that an order should be made--`
  line
  line `(a) appointing a guardian of his person or property, or both, or`
  line
  line `(b) declaring a person to be such a guardian,`
  line
  line `the Court may make an order accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under this section shall imply the removal of any guardian who has not been`
  line `appointed by will or other instrument or appointed or declared by the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a guardian has been appointed by will or other instrument or appointed or declared by`
  line `the Court, an order under this section appointing or declaring another person to be guardian in his`
  line `stead shall not be made until the powers of the guardian appointed or declared as aforesaid have`
  line `ceased under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43359)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Persons entitled to apply for order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43359&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `An order shall not be made under the last foregoing`
  line `section except on the application of—`
  line
  line `(a) the person desirous of being, or claiming to be, the guardian of the minor, or`
  line
  line `(b) any relative or friend of the minor, or`
  line
  line `(c) the Collector of the district or other local area within which the minor ordinarily resides or`
  line `in which he has property, or`
  line
  line `(d) the Collector having authority with respect to the class to which the minor belongs.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43360)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Court having jurisdiction to entertain application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43360&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the application is with respect to`
  line `the guardianship of the person of the minor, it shall be made to the District Court having jurisdiction`
  line `in the place where the minor ordinarily resides.`
  line
  line `(2) If the application is with respect to the guardianship of the property of the minor, it may be`
  line `made either to the District Court having jurisdiction in the place where the minor ordinarily resides or`
  line `to a District Court having jurisdiction in a place where he has property.`
  line
  line `(3) If an application with respect to the guardianship of the property of a minor is made to a`
  line `District Court other than that having jurisdiction in the place where the minor ordinarily resides, the`
  line `Court may return the application if in its opinion the application would be disposed of more justly or`
  line `conveniently by any other District Court having jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43361)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Form of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43361&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the application is not made by the Collector, it shall be by`
  line `petition signed and verified in manner prescribed by the ^1Code ,of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) for`
  line `the signing and verification of a plaint, and stating, so far as can be ascertained--`
  line
  line `(a) the name, sex, religion, date of birth and ordinary residence of the minor;`
  line
  line `(b) where the minor is a female, whether she is married, and, if so, the name and age of her husband;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature, situation and approximate value of the property, if any, of the minor;`
  line
  line `(d) the name and residence of the person having the custody or possession of the person or property of the minor;`
  line
  line `(e) what near relations the minor has, and where they reside;`
  line
  line `(f) whether a guardian of the person or property, or both, of the minor has been appointed by any person entitled or claiming to be entitled by the law to which the minor is subject to make such an appointment;`
  line
  line `(g) whether an application has at any time been made to the Court or to any other Court with respect to the guardianship of the person or property, or both, of the minor, and, if so, when, to what Court and with what result;`
  line
  line `(h) whether the application is for the appointment or declaration of a guardian of the person of the minor, or of his property, or of both;`
  line
  line `(i) where the application is to appoint a guardian, the qualifications of the proposed guardian;`
  line
  line `(j) where the application is to declare a person to be a guardian, the grounds on which that`
  line `person claims;`
  line
  line `(k) the causes which have led to the making of the applications; and`
  line
  line `(l) such other particulars, if any, as may be prescribed or as the nature of the application renders it necessary to state.`
  line
  line `(2) If the application is made by the Collector, it shall be by letter addressed to the Court and`
  line `forwarded by post or in such other manner as may be found convenient, and shall state as far as`
  line `possible the particulars mentioned in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The application must be accompanied by a declaration of the willingness of the proposed`
  line `guardian to act and the declaration must be signed by him and attested by at least two`
  line witnesses.
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43362)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure on admission of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43362&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Court is satisfied that there is ground for proceeding on the application, it shall fix a day for the hearing thereof, and cause notice of the`
  line `application and of the date fixed for the hearing—`
  line
  line `(a) to be served in the manner directed in the ^1Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) on—`
  line
  line `(i) the parents of the minor if they arc residing in ^2`
  line `[any State to which this Act extends,]`
  line
  line `(ii) the person, if any, named in the petition or letter as having the custody or possession of`
  line `the person or property of the minor,`
  line
  line `(iii) the person proposed in the application or letter to be appointed or declared guardian,`
  line `unless that person is himself the applicant, and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other person to whom, in the opinion of the Court, special notice of the application`
  line `should be given; and`
  line
  line `(b) to be posted on some conspicuous part of the court-house, and of the residence of the minor,`
  line `and otherwise published in such manner as the Court, subject to any rules made by the High Court`
  line `under this Act, thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by general or special order, require that, when any part of the`
  line `property described in a petition under section 10, sub-section (1), is land of which a Court of Wards`
  line `could assume the superintendence, the Court shall also cause a notice as aforesaid to be served on the`
  line `Collector in whose district the minor ordinarily resides, and on`
  line
  line `every Collector in whose district any portion of the land is situate, and the Collector may cause the`
  line `notice to be published in any manner he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) No charge shall be made by the Court or the Collector for the service or publication of any`
  line `notice served or published under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43407)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make interlocutory order for production of minor and interim protection of person and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43407&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court may direct that the person, if any, having the custody of the minor shall produce him or cause him to be produced at such place and time and before such person as it appoints, and may make such order for the temporary custody and protection of the person or property of the minor as it thinks proper.`
  line
  line `(2) If the minor is a female who ought not to be compelled to appear in public, the direction under sub-section (1) for her production shall require her to be produced in accordance with the customs and manners of the country.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall authorise—`
  line
  line `(a) the Court to place a female minor in the temporary custody of a person claiming to be her`
  line `guardian on the ground of his being her husband, unless she is already in his custody with the`
  line `consent of her parents, if any, or`
  line
  line `(b) any person to whom the temporary custody and protection of the property of a minor is`
  line `entrusted to dispossess otherwise than by due course of law any person in possession of any of the`
  line property.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43364)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Hearing of evidence before making of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43364&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `On the day fixed for the hearing of the`
  line `application, or as soon afterwards as may be, the Court shall hear such evidence as may be adduced in`
  line `support of or in opposition to the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43365)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Simultaneous proceedings in different Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for sub-section (3).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43365&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If proceedings for the appointment or`
  line `declaration of a guardian of a minor arc taken in more Courts than one, each of those Courts shall, on`
  line `being apprised of the proceedings in the other Court or Courts, stay the proceedings before itself.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Courts are both or all subordinate to the same High Court, they shall report the case to the`
  line `High Court, and the High Court shall determine in which of the Courts the proceedings with respect to`
  line `the appointment or declaration of a guardian of the minor shall be had.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) In any other case in which proceedings arc stayed under. sub-section (1), the Courts shall`
  line `report the case to, and be guided by such orders as they may receive from, their respective State`
  line Governments]
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43366)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Appointment or declaration of several guardians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-sections (2) and (3) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43366&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the law to which the minor is`
  line `subject admits of his having two or more joint guardians of his person or property, or both, the Court`
  line `may, if it thinks fit, appoint or declare them.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) Separate guardians may be appointed or declared of the person and of the property of a minor.`
  line
  line `(5) If a minor has several properties, the Court may, if it thinks fit, appoint or declare a separate`
  line `guardian for any one or more of the properties.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (43367)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment or declaration of guardian for property beyond jurisdiction of the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43367&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the Court appoints or declares a guardian for any property situate beyond the`
  line `local limits of its jurisdiction, the Court having jurisdiction in the place where the property is situate shall, on production of a certified copy of the order appointing or declaring the`
  line `guardian, accept him as duly appointed or declared and give effect to the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (43368)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Matters to be considered by the Court in appointing guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (4) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43368&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) In appointing or`
  line `declaring the guardian of a minor, the Court shall, subject to the provisions of this section, be guided`
  line `by what, consistently with the law to which the minor is subject, appears in the circumstances to be`
  line `for the welfare of the minor.`
  line
  line `(2) In considering what will be for the welfare of the minor, the Court shall have regard to the age,`
  line `sex and religion of the minor, the character and capacity of the proposed guardian and his nearness of`
  line `kin to the minor, the wishes, if any, of a deceased parent, and any existing or previous relations of the`
  line `proposed guardian with the minor or his property.`
  line
  line `(3) If the minor is old enough to form an intelligent preference, the Court may consider that`
  line preference.
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) The Court shall not appoint or declare any person to be a guardian against his will.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (43369)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Appointment or declaration of Collector in virtue of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43369&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where a Collector is`
  line `appointed or declared by the Court in virtue of his office to be guardian of the person or property, or`
  line `both, of a minor, the order appointing or declaring him shall be deemed to authorize and require the`
  line `person for the time being holding the office to act as guardian of the minor with respect to his person`
  line `or property, or both, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43370)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Guardian not to be appointed by the Court in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 2010, s. 2 for sub-clause (b) (w.e.f. 31-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43370&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall`
  line `authorise the Court to appoint or declare a guardian of the property of a minor whose property is`
  line `under the superintendence of a Court of Wards, or to appoint or declare a guardian of the person—`
  line
  line `(a) of a minor who is a married female and whose husband is not, in the opinion of the Court,`
  line `unfit to be guardian of her person, or`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) of a minor, other than a married female, whose father or mother is living and is not, in the`
  line `opinion of the court, unfit to be guardian of the person of the minor, or.]`
  line
  line `(c) of a minor whose property is under the superintendence of a Court of Wards competent to`
  line `appoint a guardian of the person of the minor.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43371)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Fiduciary relation of guardian to ward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43371&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) A guardian stands in a fiduciary relation to his`
  line `ward, and, save as provided by the will or other instrument, if any, by which he was appointed, or by`
  line `this Act, he must not make any profit out of his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The fiduciary relation of it guardian to his ward extends to and affects purchases by the`
  line `guardian of the property of the ward, and by the ward of the property of the guardian, immediately or`
  line `soon after the ward has ceased to be a minor, and generally all transactions between them while the`
  line `influence of the guardian still lasts or is recent.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43372)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Capacity of minors to act as guardians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43372&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `A minor is incompetent to act as guardian of any`
  line `minor except his own wife or child or where he is the managing member of an undivided Hindu`
  line `family, the wife or child of another minor Member of that family.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43373)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Remuneration of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43373&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A guardian appointed or declared by the Court shall be`
  line `entitled to such allowance, if any, as the Court thinks fit for his care and paints in the execution of his`
  line duties.
  line
  line `(2) When an officer of the Government, as such officer, is so appointed or declared to be guardian,`
  line `such fees shall be paid to the Government out of the property of the ward as the State Government, by`
  line `general or special order, directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43374)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Control of Collector as guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43374&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `A Collector appointed or declared by the Court to be`
  line `guardian of the person or property, or both, of a minor shall, in all matters connected with the`
  line `guardianship of his ward, be subject to the control of the State Government or of such authority as that`
  line `Government, by ^1`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoints in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For notifications appointing authorities to whose control Collectors appointed under the Act shall be subject, see different`
  line `local R. & O.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43375)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Duties of guardian of the person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43375&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `A guardian of the person of a ward is charged with`
  line `the custody of the ward and must look to his support, health and education, and such other matters as`
  line `the law to which the ward is subject requires.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43376)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Title of guardian to custody of ward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (Act 5 of 1898).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43376&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a ward leaves or is removed from the custody`
  line `of a guardian of his person, the Court, if it is of opinion that it will be for the welfare of the ward to`
  line `return to the custody of his guardian, may make an order for his return, and for the purpose of`
  line `enforcing the order may cause the ward to be arrested and to be delivered into the custody of the`
  line guardian.
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of arresting the ward, the Court may exercise the power conferred on a`
  line `Magistrate of the first class by section 100 of the ^1Code of Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882).`
  line
  line `(3) The residence of a ward against the will of his guardian with a person who is not his guardian`
  line `does not of itself terminate the guardianship.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (43377)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Removal of war from jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43377&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A guardian of the person appointed or declared`
  line `by the Court unless he is the Collector or is a guardian appointed by will or other instrument, shall`
  line `not, without the leave of the Court by which he was appointed or declared, remove the ward from`
  line `the limits of its jurisdiction except for such purposes as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The leave granted by the Court under sub-section (1) may be special or general, and may be`
  line `defined by the order granting it.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (43378)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Duties of guardian of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43378&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A guardian of the property of a ward is bound to deal`
  line `therewith as carefully as a man of ordinary prudence would deal with it if it were his own, and,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Chapter, he may do all acts which are reasonable and proper for the`
  line `realisation, protection or benefit of the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (43379)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Powers of testamentary guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43379&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where a guardian has been appointed by will or other`
  line `instrument, his power to mortgage or charge, or transfer by sale, gift, exchange or otherwise,`
  line `immovable property belonging to his ward is subject to any restriction which may be imposed by the`
  line `instrument, unless he has under this Act been declared guardian and the Court which made die`
  line `declaration permits him by an order in writing, notwithstanding the restriction, to dispose of any`
  line `immovable property specified in the order in a manner permitted by the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (43380)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Limitation of powers of guardian of property appointed or declared by the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43380&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where a person other than a Collector, or than a guardian appointed by will or other instrument, has been appointed or declared by the Court to be guardian of the property of a ward, he`
  line `shall not, without the previous permission of the Court,--`
  line
  line `(a) mortgage or charge, or transfer by sale, gift, exchange or otherwise, any part of the`
  line `immovable property of his ward, or`
  line
  line `(b) lease any part of that property for a term exceeding five years or for any term extending`
  line `more than one year beyond the date on which the ward will cease to be a minor.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (43381)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Voidability of transfers made in contravention of section 28 or section 29.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43381&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `A disposal of`
  line `immovable property by a guardian in contravention of either of the two last foregoing sections is`
  line `voidable at the instance of any other person affected thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (43382)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Practice with respect to permitting transfers under section 29.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43382&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Permission to the`
  line `guardian to do any of the acts mentioned in section 29 shall not be granted by the Court except in case`
  line `of necessity or for an evident advantage to the ward.`
  line
  line `(2) The order granting the permission shall recite the necessity or advantage, as the case may`
  line `be, describe the property with respect to which the act permitted is to be done, and specify such`
  line `conditions, if any, as the Court may see fit to attach to the permission; and it shall be recorded,`
  line `dated and signed by the Judge of the Court with his own hand, or, when from any cause he is`
  line `prevented from recording the order with his own hand, shall be taken down in writing from his`
  line `dictation and be dated and signed by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court may in its discretion attach to the permission the following among other conditions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that a sale shall not be completed without the sanction of the Court;`
  line
  line `(b) that a sale shall be made to the highest bidder by public auction, before the Court or`
  line `some person specially appointed by the Court for that purpose, at a time and place to be`
  line `specified by the Court, after such proclamation of the intended sale as the Court, subject to`
  line `any rules made under this Act by the High Court, directs;`
  line
  line `(c) that a lease shall not be made in consideration of a premium or shall be made for such term`
  line `of years and subject to such rents and covenants as the Court directs;`
  line
  line `(d) that the whole or any part of the proceeds of the act permitted shall be paid into the`
  line `Court by the guardian, to be disbursed therefrom or to be invested by the Court on`
  line `prescribed securities or to be otherwise disposed of as the Court directs.`
  line
  line `(4) Before granting permission to a guardian to do an act mentioned in section 29, the Court`
  line `may cause notice of the application for the permission to be given to any relative or friend of the`
  line `ward who should, in its opinion, receive notice thereof, and shall hear and record the statement of`
  line `any person who appears in opposition to the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (43383)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Variation of powers of guardian of property appointed or declared by the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43383&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Where a guardian of the property of a ward has been appointed or declared by the Court and such`
  line `guardian is not the Collector, the Court may, from time to time, by order, define, restrict or extend`
  line `his powers with respect to the property of the ward in such manner and to such extent as it may`
  line `consider to be for the advantage of the ward and consistent with the law to which the ward is`
  line subject.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (43408)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Right of guardian so appointed or declared to apply to the Court for opinion in management of property, of ward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43408&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A guardian appointed or declared by the Court may`
  line `apply by petition to the Court which appointed or declared him for its opinion, advice or direction`
  line `on any present question respecting the management or administration of the property of his ward.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court considers the question to be proper for summary disposal, it shall cause a copy of`
  line `the petition to be served on, and the hearing thereof may be attended by, such of the persons interested`
  line `in the application as the Court thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The guardian stating in good faith the facts in the petition and acting upon the opinion, advice`
  line `or direction given by the Court shall be deemed, so far as regards his own responsibility, to have`
  line `performed his duty as guardian in the subject-matter of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (43385)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Obligations on guardian of property appointed or declared by the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43385&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `guardian of the property of a ward has been appointed or declared by the Court and such guardian is`
  line `not the Collector, he shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if so required by the Court, give a bond, as nearly as may be in the prescribed form, to the`
  line `Judge of the Court to ensure for the benefit of the Judge for the time being, with or without`
  line `sureties, as may be prescribed, engaging duly to account for what he may receive in respect of the`
  line `property of the ward;`
  line
  line `(b) if so required by the Court, deliver to the Court, within six months from the date of his`
  line `appointment or declaration by the Court, or within such other time as the Court directs, a statement`
  line `of the immovable property belonging to the ward, of the money and other movable property which`
  line `he has received on behalf of the ward up to the date of delivering the statement, and of the debts`
  line `due on that date to or from the ward;`
  line
  line `(c) if so required by the Court, exhibit his accounts in the Court at such times and in such form`
  line `as the Court from time to time directs;`
  line
  line `(d) if so required by the Court, pay into the Court at such time as the Court directs the balance`
  line `due from him on those accounts, or so much thereof as the Court directs; and`
  line
  line `(e) apply for the maintenance, education and advancement of the ward and of such persons as`
  line `are dependent on him, and for the celebration of ceremonies to which the ward or any of those`
  line `persons may be a party, such portion of the income of the property of the ward as the Court from`
  line `time to time directs, and, if the Court so directs, the whole or any part of that property.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (43386)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to award remuneration for auditing accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1929, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43386&sectionno=34A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[34A. Power to award remuneration for auditing accounts.—When accounts are exhibited by`
  line `a guardian of the property of a ward in pursuance of a requisition made under clause (c) of section 34`
  line `or otherwise, the Court may appoint a person to audit the accounts, and may direct that remuneration`
  line `for the work be paid out of the income of the property].`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (43387)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Suit against guardian where administration-bond was taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43387&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Where a guardian appointed`
  line `or declared by the Court has given a bond duly to account for what he may receive in respect of the`
  line `property of his ward, the Court may, on application made by petition and on being satisfied that the`
  line `engagement of the bond has not been kept, and upon such terms as to security, or providing that any`
  line `money received be paid into the Court, or otherwise as the Court thinks fit, assign the bond to some`
  line `proper person, who shall thereupon be entitled to sue on the bond in his own name as if the bond had`
  line `been originally given to him instead of to the Judge of the Court, and shall be entitled to recover`
  line `thereon, as trustee for the ward, in respect of any breach thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (43388)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Suit against guardian where administration-bond was not taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43388&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a guardian`
  line `appointed or declared by the Court has not given a bond as aforesaid, any person, with the leave of the`
  line `Court, may, as next friend, at any time during the continuance of the minority of the ward, and upon`
  line `such terms as aforesaid, institute a suit against the guardian, or, in case of his death, against his`
  line `representative, for an account of what the guardian has received in respect of the property of the ward,`
  line `and may recover in the suit, as trustee for the ward, such amount as may be found to be payable by the`
  line `guardian or his representative, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as they relate to a suit against a guardian, be`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 440 of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) as amended by`
  line `this Act^1`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now Order XXXII, rules 1 and 4(2), in the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of`
  line `1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43389)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `General liability of guardian as trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43389&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in either of the two last foregoing sections`
  line `shall be construed to deprive a ward or his representative of any remedy against his guardian, or the`
  line `representative of the guardian, which, not being expressly provided in either of those sections, any`
  line `other beneficiary or his representative would have against his trustee or the representative of the`
  line trustee.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (43390)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Right of survivorship among joint guardians.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43390&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `On the death of one of two or more joint`
  line `guardians, the guardianship continues to the survivor or survivors until a further appointment is made`
  line `by the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (43391)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Removal of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43391&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Court may, on the application of any person interested, or of its`
  line `own motion, remove a guardian appointed or declared by the Court, or a guardian appointed by will or`
  line `other instrument, for any of the following causes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for abuse of his trust;`
  line
  line `(b) for continued failure to perform the duties of his trust;`
  line
  line `(c) for incapacity to perform the duties of his trust;`
  line
  line `(d) for ill-treatment, or neglect to take proper care, of his ward;`
  line
  line `(e) for contumacious disregard of any provision of this Act or of any order of the Court;`
  line
  line `(f) for conviction of an offence implying, in the opinion of the Court, a defect of character`
  line `which unfits him to be the guardian of his ward;`
  line
  line `(g) for having an interest adverse to the faithful performance of his duties;`
  line
  line `(h) for ceasing to reside within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the Court;`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a guardian of the property, for bankruptcy or insolvency;`
  line
  line `(j) by reason of the guardianship of the guardian ceasing, or being liable to cease, under the law`
  line `to which the minor is subject:`
  line
  line `Provided that a guardian appointed by will or other instrument, whether he has been declared`
  line `under this Act or not, shall not be removed`
  line
  line `(a) for the cause mentioned in clause (g) unless the adverse interest accrued after the death of`
  line `the person who appointed him, or it is shown that that person made and maintained the`
  line `appointment in ignorance of the existence of the adverse interest, or`
  line
  line `(b) for the cause mentioned in clause (h) unless such guardian has taken up such a residence as,`
  line `in the opinion of the Court, renders it impracticable for him to discharge the functions of guardian.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (43392)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Discharge of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43392&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a guardian appointed or declared by the Court desires to resign`
  line `his office, he may apply to the Court to be discharged.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court finds that there is sufficient reason for the application, it shall discharge him, and if`
  line `the guardian making the application is the Collector and the State Government approves of his`
  line `applying to be discharged, the Court shall in any case discharge him.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (43393)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Cessation of authority of guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43393&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers of a guardian of the person cease.--`
  line
  line `(a) by his death, removal or discharge;`
  line
  line `(b) by the Court of Wards assuming superintendence of the person of the ward;`
  line
  line `(c) by the ward ceasing to be a minor;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a female ward, by her marriage to a husband who is not unfit to be guardian of`
  line `her person or, if the guardian was appointed or declared by the Court, by her marriage to a husband`
  line `who is not, in the opinion of the Court, so unfit; or`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a ward whose father was unfit to be guardian of the person of the ward, by the`
  line `father ceasing to be so or, if the father was deemed by the Court to be so unfit, by his ceasing to be`
  line `so in the opinion of the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers of a guardian of the property cease--`
  line
  line `(a) by his death, removal or discharge;`
  line
  line `(b) by the Court of Wards assuming superintendence of the property of the ward; or`
  line
  line `(c) by the ward ceasing to be a minor.`
  line
  line `(3) When for any cause the powers of a guardian cease, the Court may require him or, if he is dead,`
  line `his representative to deliver as it directs any property in his possession or control belonging to the`
  line `ward or any accounts in his possession or control relating to any past or present property of the ward.`
  line
  line `(4) When he has delivered the property or accounts as required by the Court, the Court may`
  line `declare him to be discharged from his liabilities save as regards any fraud which may subsequently be`
  line discovered.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (43394)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Appointment of successor to guardian dead, discharged or removed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43394&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `When a guardian`
  line `appointed or declared by the Cowl is discharged, or, under the law to which the ward is subject,`
  line `ceases to be entitled to act, or when any such guardian or a guardian appointed by will or other`
  line `instrument is removed or dies, the Court, of its own motion or on application under Chapter II, may, if`
  line `the ward is still a minor, appoint or declare another guardian of his person or property, or both, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (43395)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Orders for regulating conduct or proceedings of guardians, and enforcement of those orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43395&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court may, on the application of any person interested or of its own motion, make`
  line `an order regulating the conduct or proceedings of any guardian appointed or declared by the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there are more guardians than one of a ward, and they are unable to agree upon a`
  line `question affecting his welfare, any of them may apply to the Court for its direction, and the Court may`
  line `make such order respecting the matter in difference as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Except where it appears that the object of making an order under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) would be defeated by the delay, the Court shall, before making the order, direct notice`
  line `of the application therefor or of the intention of the Court to make it, as the case may be, to be given,`
  line `in a case under sub-section (1), to the guardian or, in a case under sub-section (2), to the guardian who`
  line `has not made the application`
  line
  line `(4) In case of disobedience to an order made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the order`
  line `may be enforced in the same manner as an injunction granted under section 492 or section 493 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), in a case under sub-section (1), as if the ward were the plaintiff`
  line `and the guardian were the defendant or, in a case under sub-section (2), as if the guardian who made`
  line `the application were the plaintiff and the other guardian were the defendant.`
  line
  line `(5) Except in a case under sub-section (2), nothing in this section shall apply to a Collector who is,`
  line `as such, a guardian.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (43396)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Penalty for removal of ward from jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43396&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If, for the purpose or with the effect of`
  line `preventing the Court from exercising its authority with respect to a ward, a guardian appointed or`
  line `declared by the Court removes the ward from the limits of the jurisdiction of the Court in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of section 26, he shall be liable, by order of the Court, to find not`
  line `exceeding one thousand rupees, or to imprisonment in the civil jail for a term which may extend to six`
  line months.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (43397)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for contumacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43397&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if a person having the custody of a minor fails to produce him or cause him to be produced`
  line `in compliance with a direction under section 12, sub-section (1), or to do his utmost to compel the`
  line `minor to return to the custody of his guardian in obedience to an order under section 25,`
  line `sub-section (1), or`
  line
  line `(b) if a guardian appointed or declared by the Court fails to deliver to the Court, within the time`
  line `allowed by or under clause (b) of section 34, a statement required under that clause, or to exhibit`
  line `accounts in compliance with a requisition under clause (c) of that section, or to pay into the Court`
  line `the balance due from him on those accounts in compliance with a requisition under clause (d) of`
  line `that section, or`
  line
  line `(c) if a person who has ceased to be a guardian, or the representative of such a person, fails to`
  line `deliver any property or accounts in compliance with a requisition under section 41, sub-section (3), the person, guardian or representative, as the case may be, shall be liable, by order of the Court, to`
  line `fine not exceeding one hundred rupees, and in case of recusancy to further fine not exceeding ten`
  line `rupees for each day after the first during which the default continues, and not exceeding five hundred`
  line `rupees in the aggregate, and to detention in the civil jail until he undertakes to produce the minor or`
  line `cause him to be produced, or to compel his return, or to deliver the statement, or to exhibit the`
  line `accounts, or to pay the balance, or to deliver the property or accounts, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person who has been released from detention on giving an undertaking under`
  line `sub-section (1) fails to carry out the undertaking within the time allowed by the Court, the Court may`
  line `cause him to be arrested and re-committed to the civil jail.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (43398)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Reports by Collectors and subordinate Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43398&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court may call upon the Collector,`
  line `or upon any court subordinate to the Court, for a report on any matter arising in any proceeding under`
  line `this Act and treat the report as evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of preparing the report the Collector or the Judge of the subordinate Court as`
  line `the case may be, shall make such inquiry as he deems necessary, and may for the pruposes of the`
  line `inquiry exercise any power of compelling the attendance of a witness to give evidence or produce a`
  line `document which is conferred on a Court by the ^1Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (43399)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Orders appealable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. The word District rep. by Act 4 of 1926, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43399&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie to the High Court from an order made by a ^1***`
  line Court,--
  line
  line `(a) under section 7, appointing or declaring or refusing to appoint or declare a guardian; or,`
  line
  line `(b) under section 9, sub-section (3), returning an application ; or,`
  line
  line `(c) under section 25, making or refusing to make an order for the return of a ward to the`
  line `custody of his guardian; or,`
  line
  line `(d) under section 26, refusing leave for, the removal of award from the limits of the jurisdiction`
  line `of the Court, or imposing conditions with respect thereto; or,`
  line
  line `(e) under section 28 or section 29, refusing permission to a guardian to do an act referred to in`
  line `the section; or,`
  line
  line `(f) under section 32, defining, restricting or extending the powers of a guardian ; or,`
  line
  line `(g) under section 39, removing a guardian ; or,`
  line
  line `(h) under section 40, refusing to discharge a guardian; or,`
  line
  line `(i) under section 43, regulating the conduct or proceedings of a guardian or settling a matter in`
  line `difference between joint guardians, or enforcing the order ; or,`
  line
  line `(j) under section 44 or section 45, imposing a penalty.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (43400)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Finality of other orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. See now s. 115 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43400&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided by the last foregoing section and by ^1`
  line `section 622`
  line `of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), an order made under this Act shall be final and shall not`
  line `be liable to be contested by suit or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (43401)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43401&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The costs of any proceeding under this Act, including the costs of maintaining a`
  line `guardian or other person in the civil jail, shall, subject to any rules made by the High Court under this`
  line `Act, be in the discretion of the Court in which the proceeding is had.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (43402)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of High Court to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1929, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43402&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to any other power to make rules`
  line `conferred expressly or impliedly by this Act, the High Court may from time to time make rules`
  line `consistent with this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) as to the matters respecting which, and the time at which, reports should be called for from`
  line `Collectors and subordinate Courts;`
  line
  line `(b) as to the allowances to be granted to, and the security to be required from, guardians, and`
  line `the cases in which such allowances should be granted;`
  line
  line `(c) as to the procedure to be followed with respect to applications of guardians for permission`
  line `to do acts referred to in sections 28 and 29 ;`
  line
  line `(d) as to the circumstances in which such requisitions as arc mentioned in clauses (a), (b), (c)`
  line `and (d) of section 34 should be made ;`
  line
  line `(e) as to the preservation of statements and accounts delivered and exhibited by guardians ;`
  line
  line `(ff) as to the inspection of those statements and accounts by persons interested ;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `(ff) as to the audit of accounts under section 34A, the class of persons who should be`
  line `appointed to audit accounts, and the scales of remuneration to be granted to them;`
  line
  line `(g) as to the custody of money, and securities for money, belonging to wards ;`
  line
  line `(h) as to the securities on which money belonging to wards may be invested ;`
  line
  line `(i) as to the education of wards for whom guardians, not being Collectors, have been appointed`
  line `or declared by the Court ; and,`
  line
  line `(j) generally, for the guidance of the Courts in carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Rules under clauses (a) and (1) of sub-section (1) shall not have effect until they have been`
  line `approved by the State Government, nor shall any rule under this section have effect until it has been`
  line `published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (43403)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Applicability of Act to guardians already appointed by Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365&sectionId=43403&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00047_189008_1523274313365
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `A guardian appointed by,`
  line `or holding a certificate of administration from, a Civil Court under any enactment repealed by this Act`
  line `shall, save as may be prescribed, be subject to the provisions of this Act, and of the rules made under`
  line `it, as if he had been appointed or declared by the Court under Chapter II.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (43404)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title [Repealed.].
